commit.message:
Remove obsolete on disk dimm database code

Hasn't been used for a long time, using the in memory database
(memdb.c) instead.
page.c: Disable gcc warnings
page.c: Remove obsolete comment
mcelog: Fix clang warnings

mcelog: mempage_replace missing initialization of mempage fields

We hit a bug where when mcelog sees enough CE events for unique page
addresses that exceed max_corr_err_counters and starts reusing mempage
structs from previously used mempage_cluster linked
to mempage_cluster_lru_list, then some fields are not correctly reset,
which may lead to issues, eg, if the reused mempage struct was previously
used for a page that was offlined, then the newly reused mempage will have
that flag set and will prevent the new page from being offlined if required.

We fixed it with the attached patch.

mcelog: Add third model number for Arrowlake

Signed-off-by: Tony Luck <tony.luck@intel.com>

mcelog: Add kernel CONFIG message if /dev/mcelog isn't found

Linux kernel made support for /dev/mcelog optional in v4.12. Most
distributions built with CONFIG_X86_MCELOG_LEGACY=y for a while.
But some have started to drop it.

When /dev/mcelog cannot be opened, provide an extra message to tell
users to check if their kernel is built with this option.

Signed-off-by: Tony Luck <tony.luck@intel.com>

commit.message:
mcelog: New model number for Arrowlake

Signed-off-by: Tony Luck <tony.luck@intel.com>

mcelog: Don't overwrite model number when lookup fails

When converting to table driven generation of mappings between model
numbers and names etc. the new code overwrote the model number that
was found in the "struct mce" with the return value from
lookup_intel_cputype(). If that function succeeded, everything worked
well. But if it failed, then mcelog would print:

 mcelog: Unknown Intel CPU type family 6 model 4294967295

That huge number is the unsigned 32-bit value for "-1", the
error return value from lookup_intel_cputype().

Save the return from lookup_intel_cputype() in a separate variable.

Fixes: 9aee26472b2b ("mcelog: Add CPU model numbers to table and generate switch function")
Signed-off-by: Tony Luck <tony.luck@intel.com>

mcelog: Add Graniterapids, Grandridge and Sierraforest

Just add the model numbers here to avoid the message about unknown
model only decoding architectural errors. These should get more model
specific decoding later.

as Sapphire Rapids. Can fix later if there are some corner cases.

mcelog: Add decode support for Sapphire Rapids

Sapphire rapids had previously been added as if if used all the same
error codes as earlier 10nm processors. But there are sufficient
differences to justify a new set of decode functions.
